                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                    (33, 1, '2023-05-04 22:59:10', '2023-05-04 19:59:10', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Good day. My name is Pavel Karpunin and I graduated from the Hillel computer school with a degree in PHP development in 2021. Previously, I worked as a second officer on a large vessel, but I decided to change my profession and started working as a freelancer on Upwork. Currently, I am self-studying PHP and also taking courses in this language. Lately, I have been devoting all my free time to learning programming.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I created a personal pet project - a blog for PHP interviews. Initially, I planned to create it in pure PHP, then create an application using the MVC pattern, and then move it to WordPress. However, at the first stage of creating the application, I faced a dilemma: I wanted to add more functionality and from my own experience, I understood why the SOLID principle is needed. Therefore, I started the project on WordPress, as it was easier than creating everything from scratch.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You can see this project on my <a href=\"https://github.com/KarpuninP/mini_blog\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">GitHub</a> profile</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If you are interested in my resume, please let me know.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Thank you for visiting my blog.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'About me', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'about', '', '', '2023-05-10 15:14:23', '2023-05-10 12:14:23', '', 0, 'http://localhost/?page_id=33', 0, 'page', '', 0),
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                    (34, 1, '2023-05-04 22:59:10', '2023-05-04 19:59:10', '', 'Про автора', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '33-revision-v1', '', '', '2023-05-04 22:59:10', '2023-05-04 19:59:10', '', 33, 'http://localhost/?p=34', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                    (36, 1, '2023-05-10 14:42:26', '2023-05-10 11:42:26', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Тут будет текст про меня</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Про автора', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '33-revision-v1', '', '', '2023-05-10 14:42:26', '2023-05-10 11:42:26', '', 33, 'http://localhost/?p=36', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                    (37, 1, '2023-05-10 15:08:13', '2023-05-10 12:08:13', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Тут будет текст про меня</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Good day. My name is Pavel Karpunin and I graduated from the Hillel computer school with a degree in PHP development in 2021. Previously, I worked as a second officer on a large vessel, but I decided to change my profession and started working as a freelancer on Upwork. Currently, I am self-studying PHP and also taking courses in this language. Lately, I have been devoting all my free time to learning programming.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I created a personal pet project - a blog for PHP interviews. Initially, I planned to create it in pure PHP, then create an application using the MVC pattern, and then move it to WordPress. However, at the first stage of creating the application, I faced a dilemma: I wanted to add more functionality and from my own experience, I understood why the SOLID principle is needed. Therefore, I started the project on WordPress, as it was easier than creating everything from scratch.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You can see this project on my GitHub profile: <a href=\"https://github.com/KarpuninP/mini_blog\">https://github.com/KarpuninP/mini_blog</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If you are interested in my resume, please let me know.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Thank you for visiting my blog.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'About me', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '33-revision-v1', '', '', '2023-05-10 15:08:13', '2023-05-10 12:08:13', '', 33, 'http://localhost/?p=37', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                    (38, 1, '2023-05-10 15:09:22', '2023-05-10 12:09:22', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Good day. My name is Pavel Karpunin and I graduated from the Hillel computer school with a degree in PHP development in 2021. Previously, I worked as a second officer on a large vessel, but I decided to change my profession and started working as a freelancer on Upwork. Currently, I am self-studying PHP and also taking courses in this language. Lately, I have been devoting all my free time to learning programming.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I created a personal pet project - a blog for PHP interviews. Initially, I planned to create it in pure PHP, then create an application using the MVC pattern, and then move it to WordPress. However, at the first stage of creating the application, I faced a dilemma: I wanted to add more functionality and from my own experience, I understood why the SOLID principle is needed. Therefore, I started the project on WordPress, as it was easier than creating everything from scratch.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You can see this project on my GitHub profile</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If you are interested in my resume, please let me know.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Thank you for visiting my blog.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'About me', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '33-revision-v1', '', '', '2023-05-10 15:09:22', '2023-05-10 12:09:22', '', 33, 'http://localhost/?p=38', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                    (39, 1, '2023-05-10 15:10:28', '2023-05-10 12:10:28', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Good day. My name is Pavel Karpunin and I graduated from the Hillel computer school with a degree in PHP development in 2021. Previously, I worked as a second officer on a large vessel, but I decided to change my profession and started working as a freelancer on Upwork. Currently, I am self-studying PHP and also taking courses in this language. Lately, I have been devoting all my free time to learning programming.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I created a personal pet project - a blog for PHP interviews. Initially, I planned to create it in pure PHP, then create an application using the MVC pattern, and then move it to WordPress. However, at the first stage of creating the application, I faced a dilemma: I wanted to add more functionality and from my own experience, I understood why the SOLID principle is needed. Therefore, I started the project on WordPress, as it was easier than creating everything from scratch.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You can see this project on my <a href=\"https://github.com/KarpuninP/mini_blog\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">GitHub</a> profile</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If you are interested in my resume, please let me know.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Thank you for visiting my blog.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'About me', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '33-revision-v1', '', '', '2023-05-10 15:10:28', '2023-05-10 12:10:28', '', 33, 'http://localhost/?p=39',